    <title>Garlic Chilli Chard</title>

    <comment>c/o Irena Macri</comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    



    <ingredient>1 bunch Swiss or Rainbow Chard</ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 Tbsp olive oil</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 long red chilli finely chopped </ingredient>
    <ingredient>2 cloves of garlic diced</ingredient>
    <ingredient>salt and pepper</ingredient>
    <ingredient>Juice of 1/2 lemon </ingredient>

    <step>
Heat olive oil in a large fry pan. Add the chilli and garlic and stir for 10-20 seconds.  Add the chard, including the stalks, salt and pepper and the lemon juice. Stir for about 3-4 minutes over medium heat. Serve hot as a side dish - very delicious.
    </step>
</recipe>